Indian CPCB AQI levels. 
Source National Ambient Air Quality Index by Central Pollution Control Board.
RangeCategoryPossible health impacts
0–50GoodMinimum impact
51–100SatisfactoryMinor breathing discomfort to sensitive people
101–200ModerateMay cause breathing discomfort to people with lung diseases such as asthma and discomfort to people with heart disease in children and older adults
